The loop header 'for (i = 0; i < len; ++i)' sets the loop counter and the conditions themselves are acceptable, but the loop body also modifies the loop counter 'i' (several occurrences of '++i' and '++i' and an explicit '++i' in the else branch). This violates Rule 14.2 clause that the loop counter shall not be modified in the for loop body (and effectively produces multiple modifications of the counter per iteration).
